<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 12 at 3:09AM PDT  by NWS Elko</headline>
<description>...More snow showers and gusty winds today...
More snow showers expected today, but accumulations should remain
light, generally under an inch. Gusty winds expected through the
day as well, generally from the west 20-30 mph gusting 35-45 mph.
Some stronger gusts possible over Pequop Summit and downwind of
the Ruby Mountains and East Humboldt Range. Dangerous crosswinds
possible for travelers on north to south roadways. The gusty
winds could also result in some blowing and drifting of snow,
further adding to the hazardous travel conditions.
Visit www.weather.gov/elko for the latest weather information.</description>
